1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 13A-105, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 13A-105. Candidates for member of the board of
4 education of every school district or technology center school
5 district shall file declarations of candidacy in the same place and
6 with the same officials as candidates for county office. The
7 declaration of candidacy to be signed by the candidate shall have an
8 attachment to be signed by the candidate listing the requirements of
9 a candidate for election or reelection to a school board as set
10 forth in Sections 13A-106 and 5-105a of this title and Sections 5-
11 110, 5-110.1, and 5-113 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes, and
12 the candidate shall swear or affirm that he or she is eligible to
13 run for the office or serve in the office if elected. Candidates
14 shall file no earlier than 8:00 a.m. on the first Monday second
15 Wednesday in December April through no later than 5:00 p.m. on the
16 following Wednesday next succeeding Friday. For school districts
17 and technology center school districts located in more than one
18 county, filing may be either in the county wherein supervision of
19 the district is located or in the county where the candidate
20 resides.
21 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
